The paper deals with computational complexity of transversal problems in graphs, which is a topic in discrete mathematics (cs.DM). The paper also uses known results on the price of connectivity, which is a topic in computational complexity theory (cs.CC). The problems studied in the paper involve graphs and their structures, which falls under computational geometry (cs.CG) and data structures (cs.DS). Finally, the paper deals with graph theory and combinatorial optimization, which is a topic in graph theory (cs.GT).
